brewery.brewery_description: West Perth craft brewery with 450 seats, big screens, and beer garden (with kids play area) that loves to experiment and make beers that 'live on the edge'. We have 20 beers on tap and an extensive wine and cocktail list. Our award-winning kitchen delivers incredible pan-Asian cuisine, with Express Lunch Specials. We love 'Building a Culture of Good Times', and can host large corporate, birthday and social gatherings.

beer.beer_description: This is a big time hazy loaded with Nectaron, Citra and Eldorado, it is huge pineapple, passionfruit and stonefruit with a touch of sweetness. (Contains Lactose)
This thick n juicy NEIPA is packed full of Zamba, Citra and Strata which combine together to hit you with a tropical fruit burst.
Loaded with some of our favourite hops, with Citra, Eclipse, and Simcoe, this one has big citrus vibes with orange and grapefruit offset by a punchy bitterness.
Think bubblegum in a can - this is it! Made with Amarillo Hops and real strawberries, this sour is Phat fan favourite.
Red IPA packed full of Citra, Mosaic and Eldorado that are balanced by a malty backbone.
Loaded with Nectaron, this is a smooth and silky oatcream IPA. Nectaron has been paired with Citra and Eldorado along with a hint of vanilla to make it a decadent delight.
Packed full of Amarillo, Mosaic and El Dorado hops this is one hell of a pale ale. It's OG and delivers exactly what it promises.
This is a decadent chocolate stout - featuring East Kent Goldings Hops - with a lovely orange note and a touch of bitterness that leaves you wanting more. You have to love a Choc Orange!
Punchy Xtra Phat Ale full of passionfruit, stonefruit and grapefruit from some of our fave hops Galaxy, Citra and Eclipse.

Traditionally made Scwartzbier Dark chocolate, Bread crust, coffee, caramel roast dominate the aroma. Flavour up front is dark chocolate, Roast grain, hint of espresso and caramel with the hops complimenting the dark grains a clean lager profile. Black with Ruby red highlights and tan head. For a beer so dark you think it would be thick like a stout but it’s a very enjoyable beer to drink.
This beer provides a beautiful balance of the bitterness from the coffee to the sweetness of the lactose. We like to to think it provides a little ride for your taste buds.
Packed full of Mangoes and Amarillo hops, this is a thick creamy beer that hits you in the face with mango goodness and is offset by a lovely bit of vanilla.
Superphitz is showcasing the new hop Superdelic from NZ and is packed full of stonefruit and mango, with a touch of candy.
This one is our tip of the hat to how bloody good WA produce is, this crispy smashable Lager uses all WA grains from Mallokup Malt and hops from Margaret River Hops.
Toffee Apple Sour that packs big hit of toffee and finishes with bright sourness that makes it infinitely sessionable.
Beautiful creamy hazy ale is packed full of strawberries which is balanced by a light creaminess - soft as silk!
This one is a party in your mouth, 350kgs of strawberries and raspberries combined with more than 100kg of citrus and some lactose. Its zingy, tart, sour n sweet. Think fruit salad lollies

Our third annual Phatabulous™ NZ Nitro Red IPA collab release with our mates at Copper & Oak Liquor Merchants is showcase of the boldest new hops coming out of Aotearoa on a creamy Nitro Red IPA

 

This year, we’ve gone even deeper into the hop fields, with our friends from Bintani and NZ Hops, using BRĀCT NZ-106, a brand-new experimental variety so fresh it doesn’t even have a name yet! Expect bursts of zesty lime, grapefruit, and tropical punch layered over Maris Otter malt’s rich layers of caramel and toasted bread crust. New Zealand Nectaron® and Superdelic™ hops back it up with waves of mango, red berries and citrus.

Shake the can three times and dump pour for best results. Let's go NZ Nitro!
This mocha stout is the pick me up we all need, lovely rich coffee bitterness is offset by sweetness with some hints of choc and vanilla. Everyone loves a mocha right?

A bright and lively New Zealand-inspired Cold IPA with a punch of tropical fruit and crisp hop bitterness. The combination of Waimea, Motueka, and Nelson hops creates a vibrant hop profile, balanced by a lean malt bill and clean fermentation, making this a dangerously drinkable brew at 6.0% ABV.
As cold as a Cold IPA gets, this one features Amarillo and El Dorado hops, and the perfect amount of bitterness to leave you wanting more.

beer.beer_name: Beauregarde Blueberry Pie and Cream Sour
beer.beer_description: Anyone who loves Willy Wonka, will no doubt hold a soft spot for this little number. It brings all the blueberries you could ask for, and washes them down with a creamy mouthfeel leaving you to savour the last of the pastry crust.
Dip-hopped with Krush, a fresh new hop variety, this beast is bursting with punchy tropical, citrus, and berry aromas, balanced by a bold, bitter, and refreshing finish.

Happy 40th birthday AL!

Three years ago we were coming down from the high of winning Margaret River Brewhouse backyard brewing comp... this year we were celebrating Little Al's 40th at our very own brewery, with his very own birthday brew!

Little Al's Big Citra, is a big 7% IPA with a big punch of Citra. No fuss, and no words needed, bit like our Al. His review: "It's pretty good"!

Anyway, what a difference 3 years makes!
- no more homebrewing for us
- we own a bloody brewery!
- Steve Booth  has less hair 
- Travis Moore has more hair

What hasn't changed:
- Little Al's dance moves
- Little Al's beer reviews
